<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Description==
</div>

La commande [[Image:SheetMetal_AddHem.svg|24px]] '''SheetMetal Plis'''permet de créer des plis sur les bords des surfaces sélectionnées. En modifiant la propriété {{PropertyData|angle}}, un bord peut être transformé en pli.

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
A '''hem''' usually consists of a cylindrical bend of roughly 180° and a planar strip (wall).
</div>

[[Image:SheetMetal_AddWall-14.png|200px]] [[Image:Button_right.svg|16px|link=]]
[[Image:SheetMetal_AddWall-15.png|200px]]

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Caption|Two selected edges → two mitered hems}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Usage==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Select one or more edges of a solid shape.
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:SheetMetal_AddHem.svg|16px]] [[SheetMetal_AddHem|Make Hem]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Sheet Metal → [[Image:SheetMetal_AddHem.svg|16px]] Make Hem}} option from the menu.
#* Right-click in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]] or the [[3D_View|3D View]] and select the {{MenuCommand|Sheet Metal → [[Image:SheetMetal_AddHem.svg|16px]] Make Hem}} option from the context menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|Z}}.
# A '''Hem''' object is created that consists of one new hem at each selected edge, and the '''Hem properties''' [[Task_Panel|Task Panel]] opens:
#*With the '''General''' tab selected:
#** Optionally press the {{Button|Select}} button to add more edges.
#*** Optionally press the {{Button|Clear selection}} button to clear the list of selected edges.
#*** Press the {{Button|Preview}} button to finish the selection and display the changes.
#** Optionally adjust the bend parameters in this tab. See the [[#General|General]] section of the Task Panel description below
#* Optionally switch to another tab to adjust more parameters. See [[#Offsets|Offsets]], or [[#Miter|Miter]], section of the Task Panel description below.
# Press the {{Button|OK}} button to finish the command and close the Task Panel.
# Optionally adjust the parameters in the [[Property_View|Property View]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Task Panel===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Double-click an existing Hem object in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]] to re-open the Task Panel and edit the parameters.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====General====
</div>

[[Image:SheetMetal_AddHem-Task1.png|260px]]


<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* {{Button|Select}}: Changes the amount of edges in the '''base Object''' property.
* '''Type''': Sets the '''HemType''' property.
** '''Flat''' activates these sub-options:
*** '''Width''': Sets the '''width''' property.
*** {{Button|[[Image:Invert_On.svg|16px]] Reverse the wall}}: Toggles the '''invert''' property.
*** '''Width includes bend''': Toggles the '''Include Bend''' property.
** '''Open''': activates these sub-options:
*** '''Width''': Sets the '''width''' property.
*** {{Button|[[Image:Invert_On.svg|16px]] Reverse the wall}}: Toggles the '''invert''' property.
*** '''Width includes bend''': Toggles the '''Include Bend''' property.
*** '''Opening''': Sets the '''opening''' property.
** '''Tear Drop''': activates these sub-options:
*** '''Width''': Sets the '''width''' property.
*** {{Button|[[Image:Invert_On.svg|16px]] Reverse the wall}}: Toggles the '''invert''' property.
*** '''Width includes bend''': Toggles the '''Include Bend''' property.
*** '''Bend radius''': Sets the '''radius''' property.
*** '''Open''': Toggles the '''opened''' property.
**** '''Opening''': Sets the '''opening''' property.
** '''Rolled''': activates these sub-options:
*** '''Bend radius''': Sets the '''radius''' property.
*** '''Open''': Toggles the '''opened''' property.
**** '''Roll angle''': Sets the '''Roll Angle''' property.
* '''Position''': Sets the '''Bend Type''' property.
* '''Unfold''': Toggles the '''unfold''' property.
</div>


<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====Offsets====
</div>

[[Image:SheetMetal_AddHem-Task2.png|260px]]

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* '''Gap A''': Sets the '''gap1''' property.
* '''Gap B''': Sets the '''gap2''' property.
* '''Rectangle''' and '''Round''' radio buttons:  Toggle the '''relief Type''' property.
* '''Width''': Sets the '''reliefw''' property.
* '''Depth''': Sets the '''reliefd''' property.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====Miter====
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
(Not available for rolled hems)
</div>

[[Image:SheetMetal_AddHem-Task3.png|260px]]

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* '''Auto Miter''': Toggles the '''Auto Miter''' property.
*: If checked:
** '''Minimum Gap''': Sets the '''minGap''' property.
** '''Max Extend Distance''': Sets the '''max Extend Dist''' property.
*: If unchecked:
** '''Angle 1''': sets the '''miterangle1''' property.
** '''Angle 2''': sets the '''miterangle2''' property.
</div>


<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Notes==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* See [[SheetMetal_Workbench#Create_a_sheet_metal_object|Create a sheet metal object]] for a basic workflow.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Properties==
</div>


<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
See also: [[Property_View|Property View]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
A SheetMetal '''Hem''' object is derived from a [[Part_Feature|Part Feature]] object or, if it is inside a [[PartDesign_Body|PartDesign Body]], from a [[PartDesign_Feature|PartDesign Feature]] object, and inherits all its properties. It also has the following additional properties:
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Data===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Properties_Title|Parameters}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* {{PropertyData|Bend Type|Enumeration}}: "Bend Type". {{value|Material Outside}} (default), {{value|Material Inside}}, {{value|Thickness Outside}}.
* {{PropertyData|Hem Type|Enumeration}}: "Type of Hem". {{value|Flat}} (default), {{value|Open}}, {{value|Teardrop}}, {{value|Rolled}}.
* {{PropertyData|Include Bend|Bool}}: "Width includes bend geometry". Default: {{FALSE}}.
* {{PropertyData|Roll Angle|Angle}}: "Roll Angle". Default angle: {{value|90,00°}}.
* {{PropertyData|base Object|LinkSub}}: "Base Object". Link to the planar face to receive a hem.
* {{PropertyData|gap1|Distance}}: "Gap from Left side". Default: {{value|0,00 mm}}.
* {{PropertyData|gap2|Distance}}: "Gap from Right side". Default: {{value|0,00 mm}}.
* {{PropertyData|invert|Bool}}: "Invert Bend Direction". Default: {{FALSE}}.
* {{PropertyData|opened|Bool}}: "Opened Hem". Default: {{FALSE}}.
* {{PropertyData|opening|Length}}: "Openening. of Hem". Default: {{value|1,00 mm}}
* {{PropertyData|radius|Length}}: "Bend Radius", the default value depends on the radius property of the parent feature: 
* {{PropertyData|width|Length}}: "Width of Wall". Default: {{value|10,00 mm}}.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Properties_Title|Parameters Ex}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* {{PropertyData|Auto Miter|Bool}}: "Enable Auto Miter". Default: {{TRUE}}.
* {{PropertyData|kfactor|FloatConstraint}}: "Location of Neutral Line. Caution: Using ANSI standards, not DIN.". </br> Default: {{value|0,50}}. K factor (also known as neutral factor) for the bend. Used to calculate bend allowance when unfolding.
* {{PropertyData|max Extend Dist|Length}}: "Auto Miter maximum Extend Distance". Default: {{value|5,00 mm}}.
* {{PropertyData|min Gap|Length}}: "Auto Miter Minimum Gap". Default: {{value|0,20 mm}}.
* {{PropertyData|min Relief Gap|Length}}: "Minimum Gap to Relief Cut". Default: {{value|1,00 mm}}.
* {{PropertyData|unfold|Bool}}: "Shows Unfold View of Current Bend". Default: {{FALSE}} </br> {{TRUE}} unfolds the bend.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Properties_Title|Parameters Miterangle}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* {{PropertyData|miterangle1|Angle}}: "Bend Miter Angle from Left Side". Default angle: {{value|0,00°}}.
* {{PropertyData|miterangle2|Angle}}: "Bend Miter Angle from Right Side". Default angle: {{value|0,00°}}.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Properties_Title|Parameters Relief}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* {{PropertyData|Relief Factor|Float}}: "Relief Factor". Default: {{value|0,70}}.
* {{PropertyData|Use Relief Factor|Bool}}: "Use Relief Factor". Default: {{FALSE}}.
* {{PropertyData|relief Type|Enumeration}}: "Relief Type". {{value|Rectangle}} (default), {{value|Round}}. Enabled only when a gap value is set.
* {{PropertyData|reliefd|Length}}: "Relief Depth". Default: {{value|1,00 mm}}. Enabled only when a gap value is set.
* {{PropertyData|reliefw|Length}}: "Relief Width". Default: {{value|0,80 mm}}. Enabled only when a gap value is set.
</div>


